---
name: smoke-tests

description: |
  Errand verifying the local WireGuard endpoint is healthy. COLOCATE this
  job on the wireguard instance group (do not give it its own errand VM):
  WireGuard silently drops unauthenticated UDP, so a remote errand VM has
  nothing observable to probe. Run with:

    bosh -d <deployment> run-errand smoke-tests

  Checks: `wg show` succeeds, the interface is UP with an address, the
  UDP listen port is bound, the live peer count matches the rendered
  wg.conf, and (optionally) every peer has a sufficiently fresh
  handshake.

packages:
  - wireguard-tools

templates:
  bin/run.erb: bin/run

properties:
  wireguard.interface:
    description: |
      WireGuard interface to verify. Must match the wireguard job's
      wireguard.interface.
    default: wg0

  wireguard.listen_port:
    description: |
      UDP port expected to be bound. Must match the wireguard job's
      wireguard.listen_port.
    default: 51820

  smoke_tests.require_handshake:
    description: |
      When true, fail unless every configured peer has completed a
      handshake within handshake_max_age_secs. Leave false for
      road-warrior topologies where peers may be offline at errand time.
    default: false

  smoke_tests.handshake_max_age_secs:
    description: Maximum acceptable age of a peer handshake, in seconds.
    default: 180
